      <head>Leopoldine Konstantin</head>
      <div>
        <p>Austrian actress.</p>

        <p>Leopoldine Konstantin made her debut with the Deutsches Theater of Berlin in 1907,
          appearing in, among other plays, Frank Wedekind's <title level="m">Spring
            Awakening</title> (1907). She moved to Vienna in 1916, working in theater while also
          acting in silent movies. In 1938 she emigrated to the United States, appearing in Alfred
          Hitchcock’s film <title level="m">Notorious</title> (1946). She returned to Vienna in
          1948.</p>

        <p>Schenker, calling her “Leopoldi” (but the <title level="j">Neue freie Presse</title>
          listing confirms her identity), heard her reading sketches by Peter Altenberg and other
          writers on the radio on March 28, 1930.</p>
      </div>

